In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar. Beat in egg. Combine flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to the creamed mixture. Stir in marmalade and pecans if desired. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 in. apart onto greased baking sheets. Bake at 350 degrees F for 10-15 minutes or until golden brown. Remove to wire racks to cool. In a small mixing bowl, combine sugar, butter and orange peel. Add enough orange juice to achieve spreading consistency. Frost cooled cookies.